Because my love for you
Would break my heart in two

body:
And if you say run, I’ll run with you

And if you say hide, we’ll hide

Because my love for you

Would break my heart in two

If you should fall

Into my arms

And tremble like a flower.

blog.name: 9or10allgood
blog.title: Winter Storm Warning...
blog.description:
Just a hair older than middle-aged, mother, transplanted Georgian living in Texas. I love my son more than my life. I'm a bit of a nerd - Whovian since forever. I would say I'm in love with David Tennant but a woman my age should be beyond such shenanigans. Or so I've been told.

Also a fan of NCIS, NCIS:Los Angeles, Star Trek (in all its permutations), Top Gear UK (before the *ahem* dust up) and The Grand Tour, The Big Bang Theory, and The West Wing.

Also, The Wheel of Time. The Dragon Rides the Winds of Time - Forever.

Politically moderate, socially liberal, spiritual, sarcastic. Frustrated inventor, meteorologist wannabe. And I would go to space in a heartbeat.

Anti-Trump - now and always.

On the subject of Doctor Who and Moffat, think of me as Switzerland. Determined to remain neutral. Open to the good, acknowledging the bad, not willing to fight about it.

Have some chocolate. ;)

summary: “One belongs to New York instantly, one belongs to it as much in five minutes as in five years.”                               ...
caption:
“One belongs to New York instantly, one belongs to it as much in five minutes as in five years.”

                                                                             — Tom Wolfe

Founded in 1624, New York City has become a point of pride for America as the home to the Statue of Liberty, Empire State Building, Broadway, and more. People come from all over the globe for its people and its attractions. But for most, it’s a place for dreams; for new beginnings; for endless possibilities; for the start of a new life. New York City holds a different and indistinct meaning for everybody. What will it mean to you?

Bright Lights Big City is an appless, OC roleplay set in the five boroughs of New York City. Our doors opened in July of 2016 and have become the home of dozens of members and nearly 100 characters. We’re looking for active, dedicated writers to join our group and find their home with us in the city the never sleeps.
